\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 \
12. Are we all equal?\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Yes. In our pains and reasons to smile.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 \
13. Why do we take life for granted?\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Because it\'92s given to us just like that. We indulge in bad behaviors, turn to easy solutions to problems, let distractions get in the way and forget what\'92s important.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\qc\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b \cf0 But, most of all, we forget that this life is a gift with an expiration date.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0\fs28 \cf0 \
14. What do we need in this world?\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Less than we think.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 \
15. Can we have it all?\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 No. And we don\'92t need to.\
We have a wrong perception of what essential means. Life is about prioritizing, really. There\'92s just not enough time in a day and in a lifetime to achieve all goals, reach the top of all fields, be everywhere, become many things, etc.\
But it\'92s just enough to make something big out of it if we define what\'92s essential and dedicate enough time and energy to get it.\
Choose one thing and master it.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 \
16. Is life unfair?\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 No. We just have a broken idea of fairness.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 \uc0\u8232 17. Do people change?\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Yes. All the time. And if you\'92re not aware of it, then it\'92s in a bad way.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 \
18. Is there something more to life?\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 If you\'92re asking yourself that, then you need more meaning in your days.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Go out there, try different stuff and see what you care about, what you\'92re passionate about and what excites you. Then combine these in a unique way and make something beautiful out of that.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 \
19. Do we need to be saved?\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 There are two options. You can either ask yourself that and wait for a savior. Or you can make a plan, take action and create things that will make your life and the life of others better in some way.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 \
20. Why are some people mean?\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Because of their own insecurities and issues. They find {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://a306ea91b39bc792ee9aaf837d92d3eb40985c19-m.us-proxy.startpage.com/npd/zbepuzhpmpidztq/xxx/ST/mirxg1BULLuhQLuRl93YZGv7nw//////////blog/emotional-fitness/201103/why-do-we-hurt-each-other?SURFLY_TAB_PREFIX=_surfly_tab0"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 comfort in hurting others}}.\
But you should know it\'92s nothing personal. Keep in mind that life in their head isn\'92t easy either. So smile back to them and show compassion. Maybe that\'92s all they need.\
